<subSubSection pageNumber="300" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="300">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="300">Note:</emphasis>
Stotler &amp; Crandall-Stotler (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="300">Taxon</emphasis>
51: 628. 2003) proposed the conservation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="300">Anthoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="300">A. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as conserved type, in the belief that Schuster (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="300">J. Hattori Bot. Lab.</emphasis>
26: 299. 1963) must be accepted as having designated 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Notothyladaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Notothyladales" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="300">A. laevis</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
. However, the proposal made no reference to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Evans’">Evans'</normalizedToken>
(1918), or later, 
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
choices of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="300">A. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the proposal was subsequently withdrawn (see Zijlstra in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="300">Taxon</emphasis>
54: 525. 2005).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
